    "title": {
      "rendered": "2025 Fundraising Benchmarks: 4 Takeaways to Strengthen Your Nonprofit Campaigns"
    },
    "content": {
      "rendered": "<p><strong>Sponsored by <a href=\"https://www.raisely.com/?utm_campaign=12155932-%5BSponsored%20Content%5D%20NP%20Tech%20For%20Good%202025&amp;utm_source=co-marketing&amp;utm_medium=blog&amp;utm_term=2025-fundraising-benchmarks&amp;utm_content=textlink-raisely\">Raisely</a> \u2014 the fundraising platform built for nonprofits who want smarter campaigns, stronger donor relationships, and more impact.</strong></p>\n<hr />\n<h2><strong>Why 2025 Fundraising Benchmarks Matter for Nonprofits</strong></h2>\n<p>Before we dive in, benchmarks are a mirror and a map. They help you see where you stand and chart where you could go. Raisely\u2019s <a href=\"https://www.raisely.com/webinar/2025-fundraising-benchmarks?utm_campaign=12155932-%5BSponsored%20Content%5D%20NP%20Tech%20For%20Good%202025&amp;utm_source=co-marketing&amp;utm_medium=blog&amp;utm_term=2025-fundraising-benchmarks&amp;utm_content=textlink-2025-fundraising-benchmarks-report\"><strong>2025 Fundraising Benchmarks Report</strong></a> lands as nonprofits face economic headwinds, competing causes and rising donor expectations. Packed with the latest nonprofit fundraising statistics, the study doubles as your digital fundraising strategy guide in 2025.</p>\n<p><strong>About the Report &amp; Methodology</strong></p>\n<ul>\n<li><strong>13,000 campaigns</strong> across appeals, peer\u2011to\u2011peer, giving days and events</li>\n<li><strong>$250 million</strong> processed in the last 24 months</li>\n<li><strong>2,800 organisations</strong> around the globe</li>\n<li><strong>250 fundraising professionals</strong> from 13 countries and 30+ causes sharing qualitative insights</li>\n</ul>\n<p>All currency is in USD for apples\u2011to\u2011apples comparison. The report analysed organisations active in both 2023 and 2024 to spotlight real momentum.</p>\n<h2><strong>2024 Digital Fundraising Performance at a Glance</strong></h2>\n<p>The report shows that fundraising growth is happening, but it&#8217;s not evenly spread: <strong>49% of organizations grew their revenue in 2024, while 24% held flat, and 26% declined.</strong></p>\n<p style=\"text-align: center;\"><a href=\"https://www.raisely.com/webinar/2025-fundraising-benchmarks?utm_campaign=12155932-[Sponsored Content] NP Tech For Good 2025&amp;utm_source=co-marketing&amp;utm_medium=blog&amp;utm_term=2025-fundraising-benchmarks&amp;utm_content=imagelink-get-the-benchmarks-report\"><img data-recalc-dims=\"1\" loading=\"lazy\" decoding=\"async\" class=\"aligncenter wp-image-43409 size-full\" src=\"https://i0.wp.com/www.nptechforgood.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/04/1-Fundraising-Revenue-in-2024-Compared-to-2023-for-Nonprofits.png?resize=600%2C178&#038;ssl=1\" alt=\"Bar chart showing nonprofit fundraising revenue in 2024 compared to 2023: most reported an increase, fewer reported a decrease or staying about the same.\" width=\"600\" height=\"178\" srcset=\"https://i0.wp.com/www.nptechforgood.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/04/1-Fundraising-Revenue-in-2024-Compared-to-2023-for-Nonprofits.png?w=600&amp;ssl=1 600w, https://i0.wp.com/www.nptechforgood.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/04/1-Fundraising-Revenue-in-2024-Compared-to-2023-for-Nonprofits.png?resize=300%2C89&amp;ssl=1 300w, https://i0.wp.com/www.nptechforgood.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/04/1-Fundraising-Revenue-in-2024-Compared-to-2023-for-Nonprofits.png?resize=50%2C15&amp;ssl=1 50w\" sizes=\"auto, (max-width: 600px) 100vw, 600px\" /></a></p>\n<p>Median digital income nudged up <strong>6%</strong>, echoing 2023, but the average hides a wide range. <strong>1 in 4 nonprofits grew 75%, while the top 5% rocketed 267%</strong>, proving big leaps are possible even in tough times.</p>\n<p style=\"text-align: center;\"><a href=\"https://www.raisely.com/webinar/2025-fundraising-benchmarks?utm_campaign=12155932-[Sponsored Content] NP Tech For Good 2025&amp;utm_source=co-marketing&amp;utm_medium=blog&amp;utm_term=2025-fundraising-benchmarks&amp;utm_content=imagelink-get-the-benchmarks-report\"><img data-recalc-dims=\"1\" loading=\"lazy\" decoding=\"async\" class=\"aligncenter wp-image-43410 size-full\" src=\"https://i0.wp.com/www.nptechforgood.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/04/2-YoY-Fundraising-Growth-in-2024-compared-to-2023-for-Nonprofits.png?resize=600%2C213&#038;ssl=1\" alt=\"Chart showing nonprofit fundraising growth: median growth was 6% in both 2023 and 2024, but top 5% grew 215% in 2023 and 267% in 2024, indicating stronger gains.\" width=\"600\" height=\"213\" srcset=\"https://i0.wp.com/www.nptechforgood.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/04/2-YoY-Fundraising-Growth-in-2024-compared-to-2023-for-Nonprofits.png?w=600&amp;ssl=1 600w, https://i0.wp.com/www.nptechforgood.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/04/2-YoY-Fundraising-Growth-in-2024-compared-to-2023-for-Nonprofits.png?resize=300%2C107&amp;ssl=1 300w, https://i0.wp.com/www.nptechforgood.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/04/2-YoY-Fundraising-Growth-in-2024-compared-to-2023-for-Nonprofits.png?resize=50%2C18&amp;ssl=1 50w\" sizes=\"auto, (max-width: 600px) 100vw, 600px\" /></a></p>\n<p>Why does that spread matter? Because it proves growth isn\u2019t reserved for mega\u2011charities; it rewards clarity, focus and agility. The 2025 nonprofit benchmarks show that successful teams ran regular campaigns, carved out staff time to focus on fundraising and prioritized value over volume.</p>\n<p>Whether you&#8217;re launching an appeal, planning a peer-to-peer campaign, or looking to increase donor retention, these four takeaways will help your nonprofit stay focused, informed, and ready to grow.</p>\n<h2><strong>1. Fundraising Appeals Are Accelerating</strong></h2>\n<p>Nonprofit campaigns are raising funds earlier than ever. In 2024, the typical campaign raised <strong>75% of its total by Week 4</strong>, shaving two weeks off the average timeline from 2023.</p>\n<p style=\"text-align: center;\"><a href=\"https://www.raisely.com/webinar/2025-fundraising-benchmarks?utm_campaign=12155932-[Sponsored Content] NP Tech For Good 2025&amp;utm_source=co-marketing&amp;utm_medium=blog&amp;utm_term=2025-fundraising-benchmarks&amp;utm_content=imagelink-get-the-benchmarks-report\"><img data-recalc-dims=\"1\" loading=\"lazy\" decoding=\"async\" class=\"aligncenter wp-image-43413 size-full\" src=\"https://i0.wp.com/www.nptechforgood.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/04/3-Appeal-campaign-trajectory-for-Nonprofits.png?resize=600%2C350&#038;ssl=1\" alt=\"Line chart showing appeal campaign progress: 2024 campaigns (green line) raised funds faster and reached higher totals than 2023 campaigns (pink line) over 8 weeks.\" width=\"600\" height=\"350\" srcset=\"https://i0.wp.com/www.nptechforgood.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/04/3-Appeal-campaign-trajectory-for-Nonprofits.png?w=600&amp;ssl=1 600w, https://i0.wp.com/www.nptechforgood.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/04/3-Appeal-campaign-trajectory-for-Nonprofits.png?resize=300%2C175&amp;ssl=1 300w, https://i0.wp.com/www.nptechforgood.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/04/3-Appeal-campaign-trajectory-for-Nonprofits.png?resize=50%2C29&amp;ssl=1 50w\" sizes=\"auto, (max-width: 600px) 100vw, 600px\" /></a></p>\n<h4><strong>What\u2019s driving the pace:</strong></h4>\n<ul>\n<li><strong>Urgency techniques</strong> like <strong><a href=\"https://www.raisely.com/appeals?utm_campaign=12155932-%5BSponsored%20Content%5D%20NP%20Tech%20For%20Good%202025&amp;utm_source=co-marketing&amp;utm_medium=blog&amp;utm_term=2025-fundraising-benchmarks&amp;utm_content=textlink-matched-giving-periods-and-giving-days\">matched giving periods and Giving Days</a></strong> gets donations coming in faster.</li>\n<li><strong>Cross-channel strategy</strong> that builds early awareness on social and drives conversions via email and search.</li>\n<li><strong>Audience segmentation with tailored appeals</strong> with personalized messaging makes the ask relevant and gets higher donations.</li>\n</ul>\n<p>\ud83d\udccc <strong>Action Step:</strong> Plan your campaign rollout to peak earlier. Build momentum through a coordinated multi-channel launch and make your deadlines visible from day one.</p>\n<h2><strong>2. Layered Fundraising Strategies Multiply Campaign Results</strong></h2>\n<p>Fundraising tactics don\u2019t work in isolation. When used together, they dramatically increase results \u2014 without more ad spend or outreach.</p>\n<p style=\"text-align: center;\"><a href=\"https://www.raisely.com/webinar/2025-fundraising-benchmarks?utm_campaign=12155932-[Sponsored Content] NP Tech For Good 2025&amp;utm_source=co-marketing&amp;utm_medium=blog&amp;utm_term=2025-fundraising-benchmarks&amp;utm_content=imagelink-get-the-benchmarks-report\"><img data-recalc-dims=\"1\" loading=\"lazy\" decoding=\"async\" class=\"aligncenter wp-image-43422 size-full\" src=\"https://i0.wp.com/www.nptechforgood.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/04/4-Factors-improving-appeals-performance-for-nonprofits.png?resize=600%2C310&#038;ssl=1\" alt=\"Chart showing factors boosting appeal performance: matched giving multiplies fundraising by 3.7x, regular giving by 2.1x, and new donation forms by 1.6x.\" width=\"600\" height=\"310\" srcset=\"https://i0.wp.com/www.nptechforgood.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/04/4-Factors-improving-appeals-performance-for-nonprofits.png?w=600&amp;ssl=1 600w, https://i0.wp.com/www.nptechforgood.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/04/4-Factors-improving-appeals-performance-for-nonprofits.png?resize=300%2C155&amp;ssl=1 300w, https://i0.wp.com/www.nptechforgood.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/04/4-Factors-improving-appeals-performance-for-nonprofits.png?resize=50%2C26&amp;ssl=1 50w\" sizes=\"auto, (max-width: 600px) 100vw, 600px\" /></a></p>\n<h4><strong>Key findings from the benchmarks:</strong></h4>\n<ul>\n<li><strong>Matched giving</strong> boosts revenue by 3.7\u00d7</li>\n<li><strong>Recurring giving prompts</strong> can double total donations</li>\n<li><strong>Optimized donation forms</strong> (like <a href=\"https://www.raisely.com/online-giving?utm_campaign=12155932-%5BSponsored%20Content%5D%20NP%20Tech%20For%20Good%202025&amp;utm_source=co-marketing&amp;utm_medium=blog&amp;utm_term=2025-fundraising-benchmarks&amp;utm_content=textlink-raiselys-donation-form\">Raisely&#8217;s donation form</a>) increase revenue by 60%</li>\n</ul>\n<p>\ud83d\ude80 When nonprofits combined all three, the results were exponential.</p>\n<p>\ud83d\udccc <strong>Action Step:</strong> Before your next campaign, add a recurring giving ask, audit your donation form for friction, and align your messaging with a match period if possible.</p>\n<hr />\n<h2><strong>\ud83d\udce5 Download the Full Report</strong></h2>\n<p>Get all the data, benchmarks, and expert insights in one place. <a href=\"https://www.raisely.com/webinar/2025-fundraising-benchmarks?utm_campaign=12155932-%5BSponsored%20Content%5D%20NP%20Tech%20For%20Good%202025&amp;utm_source=co-marketing&amp;utm_medium=blog&amp;utm_term=2025-fundraising-benchmarks&amp;utm_content=textlink-download-the-2025-fundraising-benchmarks-report\"><strong>Download the 2025 Fundraising Benchmarks Report</strong></a><strong>:</strong></p>\n<p style=\"text-align: center;\"><a href=\"https://www.raisely.com/webinar/2025-fundraising-benchmarks?utm_campaign=12155932-[Sponsored Content] NP Tech For Good 2025&amp;utm_source=co-marketing&amp;utm_medium=blog&amp;utm_term=2025-fundraising-benchmarks&amp;utm_content=imagelink-get-the-benchmarks-report\"><img data-recalc-dims=\"1\" loading=\"lazy\" decoding=\"async\" class=\"aligncenter wp-image-43424 size-full\" src=\"https://i0.wp.com/www.nptechforgood.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/04/Raisely-2025-Benchmarks-Report-for-Nonprofits.png?resize=600%2C338&#038;ssl=1\" alt=\"Promotional graphic for the 2025 Fundraising Benchmarks Report, featuring trends, metrics, and predictions for nonprofits, brought to you by Raisely, Keela, and Aplos.\" width=\"600\" height=\"338\" srcset=\"https://i0.wp.com/www.nptechforgood.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/04/Raisely-2025-Benchmarks-Report-for-Nonprofits.png?w=600&amp;ssl=1 600w, https://i0.wp.com/www.nptechforgood.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/04/Raisely-2025-Benchmarks-Report-for-Nonprofits.png?resize=300%2C169&amp;ssl=1 300w, https://i0.wp.com/www.nptechforgood.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/04/Raisely-2025-Benchmarks-Report-for-Nonprofits.png?resize=50%2C28&amp;ssl=1 50w\" sizes=\"auto, (max-width: 600px) 100vw, 600px\" /></a></p>\n<hr />\n<h2><strong>3. Peer-to-Peer Fundraising In 2025 Is Evolving</strong></h2>\n<p><a href=\"https://www.raisely.com/peer-to-peer?utm_campaign=12155932-%5BSponsored%20Content%5D%20NP%20Tech%20For%20Good%202025&amp;utm_source=co-marketing&amp;utm_medium=blog&amp;utm_term=2025-fundraising-benchmarks&amp;utm_content=textlink-peer-to-peer\">Peer-to-peer (P2P) fundraising</a>\u00a0remains a powerful tool \u2014 but success depends on <strong>how</strong> you support participants.</p>\n<p>In 2024:</p>\n<ul>\n<li>Campaigns using P2P grew 18% in volume</li>\n<li>Profile activation rate held steady at 76%</li>\n<li>Dollars per participant dropped 20%, to $159</li>\n</ul>\n<p style=\"text-align: center;\"><a href=\"https://www.raisely.com/webinar/2025-fundraising-benchmarks?utm_campaign=12155932-%5BSponsored%20Content%5D%20NP%20Tech%20For%20Good%202025&amp;utm_source=co-marketing&amp;utm_medium=blog&amp;utm_term=2025-fundraising-benchmarks&amp;utm_content=textlink-2025-fundraising-benchmarks-report\"><img data-recalc-dims=\"1\" loading=\"lazy\" decoding=\"async\" class=\"aligncenter wp-image-43426 size-full\" src=\"https://i0.wp.com/www.nptechforgood.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/04/6.-Fundraising-per-activated-profile-for-nonprofits.png?resize=600%2C296&#038;ssl=1\" alt=\"Two charts comparing 2023 and 2024: profile activation rates were similar (76% vs. 75%), but 2023 raised more per profile ($308 vs. $244) than 2024.\" width=\"600\" height=\"296\" srcset=\"https://i0.wp.com/www.nptechforgood.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/04/6.-Fundraising-per-activated-profile-for-nonprofits.png?w=600&amp;ssl=1 600w, https://i0.wp.com/www.nptechforgood.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/04/6.-Fundraising-per-activated-profile-for-nonprofits.png?resize=300%2C148&amp;ssl=1 300w, https://i0.wp.com/www.nptechforgood.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/04/6.-Fundraising-per-activated-profile-for-nonprofits.png?resize=50%2C25&amp;ssl=1 50w\" sizes=\"auto, (max-width: 600px) 100vw, 600px\" /></a></p>\n<p>The 2025 peer-to-peer benchmarks only capture one side of the story. High\u2011growth orgs treat P2P as community activation, not just fundraising.</p>\n<h4><strong>What successful nonprofits are doing differently:</strong></h4>\n<ul>\n<li><strong>Focus on quality over quantity:</strong> Support a smaller group of active fundraisers with tools and encouragement</li>\n<li><strong>Holistic experience:</strong> Enable participants with educational resources and tips on how to fundraise to maximize each supporter&#8217;s potential.</li>\n<li><strong>Ongoing communication:</strong> Use email and SMS to guide fundraisers from signup to success</li>\n<li><strong>Encourage social storytelling:</strong> Help fundraisers post on social platforms with pre-built templates and tips</li>\n</ul>\n<p>\ud83d\udccc <strong>Action Step:</strong> Think beyond signups. Create a simple engagement plan that includes welcome messages, mid-campaign nudges, and a post-campaign thank you.</p>\n<h2><strong>4. From Acquisition to Retention: Value Over Volume</strong></h2>\n<p>Retention and recurring giving are now leading priorities for successful fundraising programs. Why? Because volume without strategy can drain time and resources.</p>\n<p style=\"text-align: center;\"><a href=\"https://www.raisely.com/webinar/2025-fundraising-benchmarks?utm_campaign=12155932-%5BSponsored%20Content%5D%20NP%20Tech%20For%20Good%202025&amp;utm_source=co-marketing&amp;utm_medium=blog&amp;utm_term=2025-fundraising-benchmarks&amp;utm_content=textlink-2025-fundraising-benchmarks-report\"><img data-recalc-dims=\"1\" loading=\"lazy\" decoding=\"async\" class=\"aligncenter wp-image-43428 size-full\" src=\"https://i0.wp.com/www.nptechforgood.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/04/7-What-are-your-top-fundraising-priorities-for-2025-for-nonprofits.png?resize=600%2C333&#038;ssl=1\" alt=\"Bar chart showing 2025 nonprofit fundraising priorities: top focuses are donor acquisition, donor retention, and regular giving, followed by appeals and conversion rates.\" width=\"600\" height=\"333\" srcset=\"https://i0.wp.com/www.nptechforgood.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/04/7-What-are-your-top-fundraising-priorities-for-2025-for-nonprofits.png?w=600&amp;ssl=1 600w, https://i0.wp.com/www.nptechforgood.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/04/7-What-are-your-top-fundraising-priorities-for-2025-for-nonprofits.png?resize=300%2C167&amp;ssl=1 300w, https://i0.wp.com/www.nptechforgood.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/04/7-What-are-your-top-fundraising-priorities-for-2025-for-nonprofits.png?resize=50%2C28&amp;ssl=1 50w\" sizes=\"auto, (max-width: 600px) 100vw, 600px\" /></a></p>\n<p>Acquisition without nurture pours water into a leaky bucket. The game is no longer about doing more; it\u2019s about doing it more strategically. Crafting a journey that feels intentional, seamless, and designed for meaningful engagement can increase the lifetime value of your donors and improve your ROI.</p>\n<p>The report also brings extra insights about how nonprofits are leveraging artificial intelligence. Going beyond built-in features and daily tasks, AI is powering a new approach: <em>audience-first fundraising,</em> equipping fundraisers with better signals and sharper timing for stronger performance.</p>\n<h4><strong>Key stat:</strong></h4>\n<p><strong>47% of fundraisers</strong> say AI is their top digital opportunity in 2025 \u2014 and they\u2019re using it to:</p>\n<ul>\n<li>Suggest <strong><a href=\"https://www.raisely.com/intelligent-amounts?utm_campaign=12155932-%5BSponsored%20Content%5D%20NP%20Tech%20For%20Good%202025&amp;utm_source=co-marketing&amp;utm_medium=blog&amp;utm_term=2025-fundraising-benchmarks&amp;utm_content=textlink-intelligent-donation-amounts\">intelligent donation amounts</a></strong></li>\n<li><strong><a href=\"https://www.keela.co/solutions/smart-ask-for-donations?utm_campaign=12155932-%5BSponsored%20Content%5D%20NP%20Tech%20For%20Good%202025&amp;utm_source=co-marketing&amp;utm_medium=blog&amp;utm_term=2025-fundraising-benchmarks&amp;utm_content=textlink-smart-donor-segments\">Smart donor segments</a></strong> based on behavior</li>\n<li>Create content and automate touchpoints for stronger supporter journeys</li>\n</ul>\n<p>\ud83d\udccc <strong>Action Step:</strong> Map your donor lifecycle. Focus on what happens <em>after</em> someone donates \u2014 and how you can turn that moment into a relationship.</p>\n<h2><strong>\ud83e\udded Donation Benchmarks: Use to Guide, Not Compare</strong></h2>\n<p>These global donation benchmarks are a starting point \u2014 not a scoreboard. They show what\u2019s possible and where smart strategy pays off. Use them to <strong>identify your strengths, spot gaps, and set smarter goals.</strong></p>\n<p style=\"text-align: center;\"><a href=\"https://www.raisely.com/webinar/2025-fundraising-benchmarks?utm_campaign=12155932-%5BSponsored%20Content%5D%20NP%20Tech%20For%20Good%202025&amp;utm_source=co-marketing&amp;utm_medium=blog&amp;utm_term=2025-fundraising-benchmarks&amp;utm_content=textlink-2025-fundraising-benchmarks-report\"><img data-recalc-dims=\"1\" loading=\"lazy\" decoding=\"async\" class=\"aligncenter wp-image-43430 size-full\" src=\"https://i0.wp.com/www.nptechforgood.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/04/8-Donation-amount-benchmarks-One-off-donations-for-nonprofits.png?resize=600%2C309&#038;ssl=1\" alt=\"Two charts showing one-off donation benchmarks: average donation increased from $110 in 2023 to $119 in 2024, while the most common donation amount stayed at $50.\" width=\"600\" height=\"309\" srcset=\"https://i0.wp.com/www.nptechforgood.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/04/8-Donation-amount-benchmarks-One-off-donations-for-nonprofits.png?w=600&amp;ssl=1 600w, https://i0.wp.com/www.nptechforgood.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/04/8-Donation-amount-benchmarks-One-off-donations-for-nonprofits.png?resize=300%2C155&amp;ssl=1 300w, https://i0.wp.com/www.nptechforgood.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/04/8-Donation-amount-benchmarks-One-off-donations-for-nonprofits.png?resize=50%2C26&amp;ssl=1 50w\" sizes=\"auto, (max-width: 600px) 100vw, 600px\" /></a><a href=\"https://www.raisely.com/webinar/2025-fundraising-benchmarks?utm_campaign=12155932-%5BSponsored%20Content%5D%20NP%20Tech%20For%20Good%202025&amp;utm_source=co-marketing&amp;utm_medium=blog&amp;utm_term=2025-fundraising-benchmarks&amp;utm_content=textlink-2025-fundraising-benchmarks-report\"><img data-recalc-dims=\"1\" loading=\"lazy\" decoding=\"async\" class=\"alignnone wp-image-43431 size-full\" src=\"https://i0.wp.com/www.nptechforgood.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/04/9-Average-fundraising-by-campaign-type-for-nonprofits.png?resize=600%2C253&#038;ssl=1\" alt=\"Chart comparing average fundraising by campaign type: 2024 outperformed 2023 across donation forms, appeals, ticketed events, and peer-to-peer campaigns.\" width=\"600\" height=\"253\" srcset=\"https://i0.wp.com/www.nptechforgood.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/04/9-Average-fundraising-by-campaign-type-for-nonprofits.png?w=600&amp;ssl=1 600w, https://i0.wp.com/www.nptechforgood.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/04/9-Average-fundraising-by-campaign-type-for-nonprofits.png?resize=300%2C127&amp;ssl=1 300w, https://i0.wp.com/www.nptechforgood.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/04/9-Average-fundraising-by-campaign-type-for-nonprofits.png?resize=50%2C21&amp;ssl=1 50w\" sizes=\"auto, (max-width: 600px) 100vw, 600px\" /></a></p>\n<h4><strong>From Insights to Action \u2014 Four Fundraising Planning Questions:</strong></h4>\n<p>The report shows that fundraising success \u201cis rooted in how strategically you design your campaigns, how well you understand your donors, and how intentionally you align every element of your strategy.\u201d</p>\n<p>To turn insights into action, bring to your team these quick discussion starters:</p>\n<ol>\n<li>Are we creating a fundraising experience that feels personal, or is it just a transaction? What signals are our donors sending that we might be missing?</li>\n<li>Which strategies are driving real connection, and which are just keeping us busy?</li>\n<li>If we stopped doing something next year, would our donors even notice?</li>\n<li>Where could we simplify, and where should we invest more time, care, and creativity to truly resonate?</li>\n</ol>\n<h2><strong>\ud83d\udcca Download the Full 2025 Fundraising Benchmarks Report</strong></h2>\n<p><a href=\"https://www.raisely.com/webinar/2025-fundraising-benchmarks?utm_campaign=12155932-%5BSponsored%20Content%5D%20NP%20Tech%20For%20Good%202025&amp;utm_source=co-marketing&amp;utm_medium=blog&amp;utm_term=2025-fundraising-benchmarks&amp;utm_content=textlink-download-the-2025-fundraising-benchmarks-report\"><strong>Download the 2025 Fundraising Benchmarks Report and watch the on\u2011demand webinar</strong></a> to benchmark your numbers, sharpen strategy and set targets that reflect the future of fundraising.</p>\n<p style=\"text-align: center;\"><a href=\"https://www.raisely.com/webinar/2025-fundraising-benchmarks?utm_campaign=12155932-%5BSponsored%20Content%5D%20NP%20Tech%20For%20Good%202025&amp;utm_source=co-marketing&amp;utm_medium=blog&amp;utm_term=2025-fundraising-benchmarks&amp;utm_content=textlink-download-the-2025-fundraising-benchmarks-report\"><img data-recalc-dims=\"1\" loading=\"lazy\" decoding=\"async\" class=\"aligncenter wp-image-43424 size-full\" src=\"https://i0.wp.com/www.nptechforgood.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/04/Raisely-2025-Benchmarks-Report-for-Nonprofits.png?resize=600%2C338&#038;ssl=1\" alt=\"Promotional graphic for the 2025 Fundraising Benchmarks Report, featuring trends, metrics, and predictions for nonprofits, brought to you by Raisely, Keela, and Aplos.\" width=\"600\" height=\"338\" srcset=\"https://i0.wp.com/www.nptechforgood.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/04/Raisely-2025-Benchmarks-Report-for-Nonprofits.png?w=600&amp;ssl=1 600w, https://i0.wp.com/www.nptechforgood.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/04/Raisely-2025-Benchmarks-Report-for-Nonprofits.png?resize=300%2C169&amp;ssl=1 300w, https://i0.wp.com/www.nptechforgood.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/04/Raisely-2025-Benchmarks-Report-for-Nonprofits.png?resize=50%2C28&amp;ssl=1 50w\" sizes=\"auto, (max-width: 600px) 100vw, 600px\" /></a></p>\n<div style=\"background-color: #3f69a2; padding: 4px;\"></div>\n<div style=\"background-color: #e8edf4; padding: 5px;\">\n<h2><b>About the Sponsor</b></h2>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://www.raisely.com/?utm_campaign=12155932-%5BSponsored%20Content%5D%20NP%20Tech%20For%20Good%202025&amp;utm_source=co-marketing&amp;utm_medium=blog&amp;utm_term=2025-fundraising-benchmarks&amp;utm_content=textlink-raisely\">Raisely</a></strong> is the purpose-built fundraising platform helping nonprofits turn bold ideas into high-impact campaigns. Trusted by over 3,800 nonprofits in 51 countries, Raisely powers digital fundraising that feels personal, performs exceptionally, and grows with your mission.</p>\n<p>From matched giving to peer-to-peer to recurring programs, Raisely\u2019s flexible tools and intuitive interface help teams save time, raise more, and build better donor experiences\u2014without needing a tech team. We combine best-in-class fundraising tech with human-centered support to make every campaign count.</p>\n<p>Explore how Raisely can support your next campaign at by <a href=\"https://www.raisely.com/demo?utm_campaign=12155932-%5BSponsored%20Content%5D%20NP%20Tech%20For%20Good%202025&amp;utm_source=co-marketing&amp;utm_medium=blog&amp;utm_term=2025-fundraising-benchmarks&amp;utm_content=textlink-demo-request\">signing up for a demo at Raisely.com</a>.</p>\n<div style=\"text-align: center;\"></div>\n</div>\n",
